House Speaker Jim Wright, D-Texas,said House Budget Committee Democrats were on target to reachbudget deficit reduction goals with a plan for 18 billion dlrsin new revenues and 18 billion dlrs in additional budget cuts.    "We're right on target," Wright told reporters. "The cuts arereal cuts. The revenues would be real revenues."    Wright said it would be up to Congress to come up with thenew revenues. President Reagan says he will veto anylegislation which raises taxes.    Wright said the budget plan may come up in the House nextweek. Republicans are expected to offer an alternative budget. Reuter&#3;